// Baked precomputation table for the Groth-Kohlweiss proof verifier.
//
// kVkH_baked[k] = compressed encoding of (V[k] * H), where:
//   V[k] = CryptoNote::DENOMINATIONS[k]   (k = 0..63, canonical CT denoms)
//   H    = hash_to_point("CN-amount-generator")  (the Pedersen H generator)
//
// These 64 points are constants of the protocol — they depend only on the
// denomination set and the generator domain string. Caching them in source
// turns the per-call cost of compute_derived_ring (64 variable-base
// scalarmults, ~5.4 ms each invocation) into 64 subtractions against the
// precomputed table.
//
// Audit / regeneration:
//   1) These bytes are visible in source for review.
//   2) The unit test `GKProof.BakedVkHTableMatchesFromScratch` recomputes
//      V[k]*H from CryptoNote::DENOMINATIONS[] + Crypto::pedersen_get_H()
//      every build and asserts byte-for-byte equality with this table.
//      Any change to the denomination set, the generator domain, or the
//      Edwards-curve encoding will trip the test and force regeneration.
//   3) To regenerate after such a change, run:
//          tests/Release/CTBench --print-vkh-table
//      and paste the output over the kVkH_baked array below.

#pragma once

